An android application developed for an IoT based Air and Water Quality Monitoring project. Monitoring is done by a device comprising of sensors powered by arduino. Data from device is send to a server using GSM shield. Android app directly downloads data from server for the user to view data.

Application Highlights:
    Check internet conection of phone and connect to server.
    Parse data received from server, which is in Json format.
    Create a local database on phone and save in it using MySQL.
    Send sms to device directly.
    Extract data from sms received from device.
    Uses mpchart android library to display bar and line graphs.
    Display content from local database in tabulated form.
    Read and update local database using MySQL.

Development:
    This application was developed using Android Studio.

